It's not supposed to *not* bother a person to hear that someone hates
themselves.  I certainly wouldn't want someone to think that I can sit
comfortably with those words, and I wouldn't want to behave like it's
acceptable to hear.  I'd like to think of a way to have a happy influence.

Somebody recently posted the link to a blog belonging to a musician.  It
covered the use of words like hate and should, among others.  That might
serve as an inspiration.  I didn't save it as I was flying through email and
maybe someone could repost it.

