<POSTER> &quot;Karen Tucker&quot; &lt;tuckerv...@gmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-11-18T14:46:00 </POSTDATE>
Well, there's bothering and then there's *bothering.*  There's no need to
panic at an expressed feeling.  There's no need for alarm, unless the child
is holding a gun to her head.  There *is* a need to respond.  Nothing in my
post said I could sit comfortably with those words, but I don't have to heap
my feelings about it on top to make it more than what it is.  No 7 year old
would really want to be dead.  No 7 year old is going to hate themselves
every minute of every day for the rest of their lives.  Keeping it in
perspective helps the child keep things in perspective, too.

Karen

