<POSTDATE> 2007-11-19T09:15:00 </POSTDATE>
Yes, communication.  My experience is that it's not a one-time thing.  The
first time you hear it, you have your normal reaction and surprise and
conversation, and a few more times you talk about it some more.  If a child
needs the whole long involved thing each time they say it, then by all
means....it has been my experience that a two or three word answer is
enough.  Then again, I have sons, who struggle with their feelings pretty
much solo and I only occasionally get a glimpse.  They don't want me to say
too much, ever.  This girl may be different.

Karen

