Thanks for all the responses. A breif history. This little girl got a bruise because her brother pushed her into a doorknob. The school reported when she went to school the next day and told the counselor her mother shook and pushed her into a computer desk. She has been diagnosed as bipolar and adhd.

She was in foster care for 8 months. Thrown out of 6 foster homes and finally placed into a group home.

I can really understand her saying things like I hate myself and i just want to die. I have been following a recent thread at always unschooled and I think she needs to know that I can handle her and Im not going to send her away.

I think Im going to try not making a big deal of her words and not force as if its a punishment but encourage her to join me/us in everything we do.

Her mom is trying really hard but also raising 3 singly, working and going to school fulltime so this 7 year old gets pushed aside a lot, told to go outside and play and watch her little brother etc. Mom loves this girl dearly and i think she is truly trying but she is very overwhelmed right now.

I want to build this little girl up and make her feel loved but I dont want her to prefer me/ here to mom and alienate mom/daughter even more.

